com.amplifyframework.core.model

Class AuthRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amplifyframework.core.model.AuthRule

  • public final class AuthRule
extends java.lang.Object
    AuthRule is used define an authorization rule for who can access and operate against a Model or a ModelField.
    See Also:
    GraphQL Transformer @auth directive documentation.

      • getIdentityClaimOrDefault

        public java.lang.String getIdentityClaimOrDefault()
        Used to specify a custom claim. Defaults to "username" when using AuthStrategy.OWNER. Note: An older version of the CLI incorrectly generated a value of "cognito:username" so we also check for this value and convert it to the proper default of "username" for backwards compatibility.
        Returns:
        identity claim

      • getGroupsFieldOrDefault

        public java.lang.String getGroupsFieldOrDefault()
        Used for dynamic group authorization. Defaults to "groups" when using AuthStrategy.GROUPS.
        Returns:
        name of a ModelField of type String or array of Strings which specifies a group or list of groups which should have access.

      • getGroupClaimOrDefault

        public java.lang.String getGroupClaimOrDefault()
        Used to specify a custom claim. Defaults to "cognito:groups" when using AuthStrategy.GROUPS.
        Returns:
        group claim

      • getOperationsOrDefault

        public java.util.List<ModelOperation> getOperationsOrDefault()
        Specifies which ModelOperations are protected by this AuthRule. Any operations not included in the list are not protected by default.
        Returns:
        list of ModelOperations for which this AuthRule should apply.
